VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you know how it develops. For now, let\'s go check out what Stability has been cooking. But first, so as vibe coding has become such a big thing recently, and if you\'re not aware of the term, it\'s it\'s basically building apps using'

[04:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'natural language. And to that, today, I have a very cool tool that will allow you to build your own web apps from scratch without any coding knowledge needed. And you can have it up and'

[04:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'online in just minutes. So, Hostinger, who are sponsoring today\'s video, have just launched Hostinger Horizons. This allows you to create custom and personalized web applications and deploy them with no third-party support needed.'

[04:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Hostinger Horizons is perfect for founders or solopreneurs who often need very specific web applications, but, you know, probably lack the coding skills needed to pull it off. But, what\'s really cool'

[05:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is that there are just endless ways to approach this. For example, I thought, and, you know, obviously, relevant to this channel, it would be cool to put together an AI video and image prompt builder. And sure, there are plenty of'

[05:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'prompt builders out there, but as we all know, each platform sort of has its own quirks when it comes to prompting. So, I think putting together a no-code web app is a great way of really fine-tuning'

[05:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'things to, you know, your tastes. So, kicking off, we\'ll give it the prompt, let\'s build an AI image and video prompt creator for Runway\'s Gen 3, the AI video generator, and Frames, which is their AI image generator. And then I let it know'

[05:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that down the road we\'re also going to add in some other platforms like Kling, Minimax, and Luma Labs. And maybe a few more. So, let\'s fire this off. And I\'d say in about 30 seconds, we essentially have the beginning of our prompt creator. Now, an'

[06:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'important note here is that it did give me tabs for Gen 3 and Frames here and a prompt box, but it doesn\'t really know what it\'s doing yet. And that\'s because, well, I didn\'t provide it with enough direction. So, for example, and sliding'

[06:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'over to another version of this that I\'ve spent about 15 minutes with, I would say, you know, one of the first things I had to do was let it know, you know, the idea that I would like to be able to do is type in a very basic prompt and have'

[06:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you fill it in. I then gave it essentially all of Runway Gen 3\'s documentation just to let it know, like this is how I I want the prompts to be outputted. I also added in an image reference prompt'

